						<div class="postbody">Do games that use letterboxing to increase VRAM bandwidth, like <em>Final Fight</em> and <em>Street Fighter II</em>, enable anything mid-frame? I know <em>Super Street Fighter II</em> uses both line scrolling and letterboxing. <em>Star Fox</em> rotates its backdrop with a combination of OPT and line scrolling and is also letterboxed. What does <em>Super Mario Kart</em> do? I know it has that black band between the players' views.</div>

					
