					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Hope you're not asking me.<br /><br />The big testing spree where I remembered all the obscure games with weird issues and behaviors was 7-13 years ago. I can't remember things I said or did two weeks ago anymore &gt;_&gt;<br /><br />I have a hard time believing there's no games that have a single HDMA channel disabled at V=0, and then turn it on later in the frame, when using HDMA init. And yet ... this change of behavior marks a direct incompatibility, so if they did, we would have known. So ... I don't know.<br /><br />We need to devise a way to test for this. It's tricky because DoTransfer isn't a flag you can toggle easily, it's internal state.</div>

